Abengoa Sells CEMIG Transmission Line Stake at 485 Million Euros

-- B y   R o b i n   S t r i n g e r
-- 
2011-06-02T23:30:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/abengoa-sells-cemig-transmission-line-stake-at-485-million-euros.html
Spain’s  Abengoa SA (ABG)  agreed to sell
stakes in transmission lines in  Brazil  to Compania Energetica de
Minas Gerais for 485 million euros, according to a PR Newswire
statement.  Abengoa’s estimated net gain from the sale will be between
27 million euros and 30 million euros. The deal will also reduce
Abengoa’s net debt by about 656 million euros and forms a joint
venture with CEMIG. Abengoa will also sell 100% of concession
company NTE to CEMIG.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Robin Stringer at 
 rstringer@bloomberg.net  